Title: The Man with Delicate Hands
Description: A man is burned to death in an apparent car accident but his sister knows it is not the man claimed because the body does not have delicate hands. Her brother is being tortured nearby to get information that can be used on Insider trading to make money on planned currency devaluations. Boss Henry Dickinson sends Miller on the case.
Short Description: A sister knows a man burned to death is not her brother because of his hands.

Title: The Menacing Mazurka
Description: Miller is a publicity agent to keep an eye on the (Moscow) Bassrai State Dancers visit to London. A dancer wants to defect but Miller is suspicious of her. The visit is being used to try and return a Colonel  who defected to Britain years earlier.
Short Description: Miller is a publicity agent to keep an eye on the (Moscow) Bassrai State Dancers visit to London.

Title: The Last Jump
Description: Miller and Stock join a parachute regiment where someone is killing paras and using its West Germany jumps to pass equipment to East Germany. Miller calls Carter: "Porridge" 3 times.
Short Description: Miller and Stock join a parachute regiment where someone is killing paras and using its West Germany jumps to pass equipment to East Germany.

Title: Ticket for Blackmail
Description: An exclusive tour of France run by two brothers is a front for a con game, blackmail and murder. When Craig is in trouble with the French police, his boss denies knowledge of him.
Short Description: An exclusive tour of France run by two brothers is a front for a con game, blackmail and murder.
